title: Help to create OCR systems to extract tables from images - Upwork
description:
We are looking for an expert to assist us in setting up a system to extract tables (to a csv) from images. The images are taken from screenshots of a table on a SD monitor and there will always be exactly the same table columns and headers, though the rows and cells containing data will be constantly different, including some empty cells.

There are also multiple variations of formatted colours, though our tests have shown this isn't an issue.

We have tried mainstream OCR including visual inspection using Chat GPT 4o and they are not accurate enough for our requirements. We have also tried tesseract, though this is not accurate at all out of the box and we don't think we'd need to train a model for a task this simple.

We have trialed AWS Textract and the results were accurate from the draft, though we'd need to set up something simple to automate this process and ensure we were always getting the correct columns extracted. We would also need to ensure the data is clean. We'd also be interested in finding a way to differentiate the extracted data if say, a cell had grey text rather than black text, as this varies in different tables.

In your response, tell us which approach you would use and how many hours you would expect this to take. 

I am happy to consider a fixed rate for this job as well once we have agreed to the specific requirements.

title: Developer Needed for CSV to JSON Transformation and High-Volume Data Serving (2) - Upwork
description:
We are seeking an experienced developer to help us create a serverless application within our AWS environment. The goal of this project is to periodically retrieve a CSV file from a URL, store it in S3, transform its content into a JSON feed, and efficiently serve individual objects from this feed via a query string. The response should be cached to handle high-volume traffic.

Project Requirements:

1. Retrieve CSV File:

   - Every 60 minutes download a CSV file from a specified URL.

   - Store the downloaded CSV file in an S3 bucket.

2. Transform CSV to JSON:

   - Parse the CSV content and transform it into a JSON format.

   - Each row in the CSV should be converted to a JSON object with an added unique identifier (`id`).

3. Serve JSON Data:

   - Create a function to retrieve a specific object from the JSON array based on a query string parameter (e.g., `?id=3`).

   - If no matching object is found, the function should return a random object from the array.

4. Cache Responses:

   - Implement caching for the responses to ensure the solution can handle high-volume HTTP traffic.

   - The cache should be invalidated and updated whenever the CSV file is re-downloaded and processed.

Technical Requirements:

- The solution should be built using AWS services, ideally leveraging serverless technologies such as AWS Lambda, API Gateway, and S3.

- The application should be designed for scalability and efficiency, ensuring minimal latency for data retrieval.

- Proper error handling and logging should be implemented for monitoring and troubleshooting purposes.

Deliverables:

- A fully functional serverless application deployed in our AWS environment.

- Source code with clear documentation.

- Configuration and deployment instructions.

- A brief test plan to verify the functionality of the application.

Skills Required:

- Proficiency in AWS services (Lambda, S3, API Gateway, etc.)

- Experience with serverless application development

- Strong understanding of JSON and CSV data formats

- Expertise in caching strategies for high-volume traffic

If you have experience in building scalable, serverless applications and can meet the above requirements, we would love to hear from you. Please provide examples of similar projects you have completed along with your proposal.
skills: AWS Lambda,     API Integration,     JSON,     Amazon S3

title: Experienced Tech Support Staff - Desktop Support/Office365/AWS/Azure/WordPress (PART TIME) - Upwork
description:
This job is a customer-facing tech support role. You will need to have had experience performing remote access technical support to end-users to be considered for this role.

** This is a TECHNICAL and CUSTOMER-FACING job - please do not apply if you do not have experience with BOTH of these **

Before you apply please read through all of the sections below carefully.

A. Shift Setup (Part Time)

-----------------

We are looking for an additional person across different shifts (times listed below):

Day: 8am to 4pm (AEDT) (Prefer Senior Engineers in this shift)

Evening: 4pm to 12pm (AEDT) (Prefer Jnr/Mid Level Engineers in this shift)

The shifts operate 7 days a week and you are required to be available for ALL 7 days. Weekends are on-call, meaning you don't need to be at a desk to do your work but you must be available in the designated shift block to answer calls and deal with high-priority tickets and respond to alerts.

What does Part Time mean? It is expected that 4 hours' work is completed on any weekday shift - shift reports are completed at the end of each shift. You must demonstrate that you have completed 4 hours work on every shift during the week. You must be available to take calls and answer tickets across the whole 8 hours shift block. 

All our systems come with mobile apps so doing this whilst you're on the go (but still in a quiet area when taking a call) should be ok. The arrangements above mean you could have a second contract running at the same time but it's recommended that the other contract isn't one that requires you to take calls.

B. Pay Scale

-----------------

Junior Engineer (This means you have had experience in some of the required technologies): AUD$500 per fortnight

Mid-Level Engineer (This means you have had experience in most of the required technologies): AUD$600 per fortnight

Senior-Engineer (This means you have had a solid working experience will all of the required technologies): AUD$700 per fortnight

I am open to negotiation with suitable candidates. If you like the setup and the work we're offering, put in a bid and let's have a chat. 

C. Technical Skills Required

-----------------

1. WHMCS: You must have working experience inside this tool as we use it to manage our clients and billing

2. Hubspot: We use Support, Help Center, Live Chat. You need working experience with all of these.

3. Office365: We use this ourselves and we provide support to clients who use this. This means you have had experience managing as well as using an Office365 environment. The main apps you need to know about are Outlook (mail), Office Desktop Apps, Teams, SharePoint, OneDrive

4. AWS: All of our own and our client infrastructure will operate in AWS and you will need to have had experience with deploying and managing AWS Ec2, S3 and Route53 services in AWS.

5. Acronis Cloud: We utilise this for our own backups as well and backups for clients and from Office365.

6. Trend Micro: We utilise the server and desktop variety of Trend products for our clients.

Plesk Onyx: We utilise this for our Shared Hosting platform and it's required that you have a working understanding of Plesk technologies.

7. WordPress: We build and manage WordPress websites for clients. This includes ongoing updates, security patching and performance improvement. We don't need you to be a coder but you must understand how to manage and make changes to a WordPress site.

8. TeamViewer: We use Teamviewer for ALL remote support and you must know how to use it

9. Windows Servers: For some clients and some other services we utilise Windows Servers.

10. Linux Servers: We use these for our Shared Hosting services and would required you to know how to manage and support them.

D. Candidate Requirements (All of these must be met)

-----------------

1. You must be fluent in spoken English in order to be able to hold a conversation, to be able to understand the very basics of customer service are an absolutely MUST HAVE for you to get this job. I will be asking to speak with you and anyone you intend to use to test you out.

2. You must be a faster learner and able to get into this job quickly.

3. You need to have a fast and reliable internet connection and reliable power at your location.

4. You must be an independent freelancer - we will NOT work with agencies

5. National police checks are required for this position and any candidate offered a role will need to complete a national police check through our nominated provider.

Thanks, and I look forward to seeing some strong and enthusiastic applicants!

title: Kubernetes(ARGO Template Expert) - Upwork
description: I need someone to create an Argo workflow template in YAML format to call several SQL stored procedures, both in parallel and sequentially. The DB user credentials should be parsed as a secret in the template. The first step is to schedule a check to see if it's the end of the day (considering the time of day, timezone, and day of the week). If the time is correct, proceed to the second step; otherwise, stop. The second step involves stopping services by calling a SQL stored procedure. If services are stopped successfully, continue; otherwise, fail. The third step is to take a backup by calling a SQL stored procedure on two SQL servers in parallel. If the stored procedure completes successfully, continue; otherwise, fail. The fourth step is to perform indexing by calling a SQL stored procedure on two SQL servers in parallel. If indexing completes successfully, continue; otherwise, fail. The fifth step is to start services by calling a SQL stored procedure. If services start successfully, end the process; otherwise, fail. This template should be parameterized to allow the addition of actual stored procedure names, timezone format, etc
skills: DevOps,     Kubernetes

title: CrowdStrike CNAPP Engineer (Cloud Security) To Work Via Zoom - Upwork
description:
Work will be done via zoom screen share. We are seeking a highly skilled Cloud Security Solutions Specialist to help us strengthen our cloud security posture. The ideal candidate will have extensive experience with a variety of cloud security tools and practices, including CSPM, IaC scanning, CWPP, CSNS, KSPM, CIEM, ASPM, DSPM, and CDR.

Key Responsibilities:

Cloud Security Posture Management (CSPM)

Detect, prevent, and remediate misconfigurations in cloud environments

Ensure compliance with industry regulations and standards

Provide visibility, alerts, and guided or automated remediation

Infrastructure-as-Code (IaC) Scanning

Use tools like Terraform, Serverless Framework, AWS CloudFormation, and CDKTF

Automate IaC scanning in the CI/CD pipeline

Detect vulnerabilities and misconfigurations in IaC files

Cloud Workload Protection Platform (CWPP)

Protect cloud workloads including VMs, databases, APIs, containers, and Kubernetes

Detect and correct security threats to ensure smooth production

Cloud Service Network Security (CSNS)

Implement real-time protection mechanisms like WAF, WAAP, DDOS protection, load balancing, and TLS examination

Kubernetes Security Posture Management (KSPM)

Manage Kubernetes activities and configurations

Perform environment and workload monitoring, cluster penetration testing, and benchmarking

Cloud Infrastructure Entitlement Management (CIEM)

Manage permissions and rights across multi-cloud environments

Enforce the principle of least privilege and detect unnecessary access

Application Security Posture Management (ASPM)

Secure applications in production by identifying exploitable vulnerabilities and misconfigurations

Data Security Posture Management (DSPM)

Goals

title: Time based ranges bot - Upwork
description:
To implement this trading strategy on Tradovate, we need to break it down into several parts:

1. Identifying qualified swing highs and lows.

2. Tracking qualified ranges.

3. Tracking the 50% level of the qualified ranges.

4. Entering trades based on the criteria.

Step-by-Step Implementation

1. Identify Qualified Swing Highs and Lows

Qualified Swing Highs:

* Detect consecutive bullish candles followed by a bearish candle.

* Track the highest wick between the last bullish candle and the bearish candle (expansion line).

* Track the wick of the bearish candle (correction line).

* Confirm a swing high if another bearish candle closes below the correction line before any candle closes above the expansion line.

Qualified Swing Lows:

* Detect consecutive bearish candles followed by a bullish candle.

* Track the lowest wick between the last bearish candle and the bullish candle (expansion line).

* Track the wick of the bullish candle (correction line).

* Confirm a swing low if another bullish candle closes above the correction line before any candle closes below the expansion line.

2. Track Qualified Ranges

* Identify ranges expanding between 8:00 - 8:45 AM EST and 9:10 - 9:45 AM EST.

* Ensure the range created is at least 60 points or more.

3. Track the 50% Level of the Qualified Range

* Calculate the midpoint of the identified ranges.

4. Enter Trades

* Enter a trade when the price comes back to the 50% level and creates a balanced price range imbalance.

title: Web scraping application for conference and event data extraction - Upwork
description:
Job Description: Web Scraping Application for Conference and Event Data Extraction

We are seeking an experienced developer or a no-code solution expert to build a web scraping application for our business. The application will search for and extract relevant information from various websites related to conferences, events, and continuing education opportunities in the behavioral health, legal, education, and related fields. The extracted data will be exported in a format that can be easily uploaded to our existing event management application..

Key Requirements and Functionalities

1.	Extensive Web Scraping Capabilities 

o	Scrape data from a vast number of websites (100+)

o	Navigate through complex website structures and extract data from multiple levels

o	Handle various data formats, including PDFs, images, and nested data structures

o	Implement intelligent navigation and error handling to bypass pop-ups, cookie consent forms, and other obstacles

2.	Comprehensive Data Extraction 

o	Extract detailed event information, such as target audience, CE credits, topics, call for papers/presentations, exhibit hall details, sponsorship opportunities, and more

o	Ability to define and customize data extraction rules and parameters

3.	Determination of Call for Presentations/Posters/Papers and Exhibit Hall Presence 

o	Implement logic to accurately determine the presence of a Call for Presentations/Posters or Papers for each scraped event

o	Set the corresponding field value as "Yes" or "No" in the exported data

o	Similarly, determine the presence of an Exhibit Hall, Sponsorships, or Partnerships for each event and set the appropriate field value

4.	Advanced Duplicate Detection and Data Merging 

o	Implement robust duplicate detection mechanisms to avoid redundant data

o	Merge and update existing event information with new data as it becomes available (e.g., "Call for Presentations" followed by "Save the Date" and workshop details)

5.	Admin-Facing User Interface 

o	Develop an intuitive and user-friendly interface for administrators to manage the web scraping application

o	Allow administrators to configure and modify search parameters, including target websites, keywords, and data fields

o	Provide options to schedule and trigger scraping tasks manually or at specific intervals

o	Display real-time progress and status updates for ongoing scraping tasks

o	Implement reporting functionality to generate and export scraped data reports in various formats (e.g., CSV, Excel)

6.	Data Export for Main App Integration 

o	Export the extracted event information, including the determined presence of Call for Presentations/Posters/Papers and Exhibit Hall, in a format compatible with the main app's upload process

o	Ensure that the exported data is structured and formatted correctly for seamless integration into the main app's modules

7.	Scheduling and Automation 

o	Implement an automated workflow for data extraction and export

o	Allow for scheduling of scraping tasks at specific intervals (e.g., daily, weekly, monthly)

8.	Logging and Error Handling 

o	Implement comprehensive logging and error handling mechanisms

o	Provide detailed logs for monitoring and debugging purposes

o	Handle and report any errors or exceptions gracefully

9.	Scalability and Performance 

o	Design the application to handle a large volume of websites and data efficiently

o	Optimize the scraping process for improved performance and reduced runtime

o	Implement caching mechanisms to avoid unnecessary re-scraping of unchanged data

Approach 1: Custom Development If you propose a custom development approach, please include the following in your proposal:

1.	Your experience and expertise with web scraping technologies and programming languages (e.g., Python, Scrapy, BeautifulSoup, Puppeteer, Selenium).

2.	Your familiarity with data manipulation libraries (e.g., Pandas) and regular expressions for data extraction.

3.	Your approach to building the web scraping application, including the architecture, design patterns, and libraries you would use.

4.	The estimated timeline and cost breakdown for the custom development approach.

Approach 2: No-Code Solution (ParseHub or Similar) If you propose using a no-code web scraping tool like ParseHub, please include the following in your proposal:

1.	Your experience and expertise with the specific no-code tool you recommend (e.g., ParseHub, Octoparse, Dexi.io).

2.	Examples of web scraping projects you have successfully completed using the proposed no-code tool.

3.	How you would approach building the web scraping application using the no-code tool, including any specific features or techniques you would employ.

4.	Any limitations or challenges you foresee in using the no-code tool for this project and how you would address them.

5.	The estimated timeline and cost for building the web scraping application using the no-code tool.

Deliverables

Regardless of the approach chosen (custom development or no-code), the final deliverables should include:

1.	Fully Functional Web Scraping Application: 

o	The application should meet all the specified requirements and functionalities outlined in the project description.

o	It should be able to scrape data from the targeted websites, perform data extraction, and handle data export.

o	The application should be tested and validated to ensure its accuracy, reliability, and performance.

2.	Source Code or Project Files: 

o	For custom development: 

	The complete source code of the web scraping application should be provided.

	The code should be well-structured, commented, and maintainable.

	Include any necessary configuration files, dependencies, and setup instructions.

o	For no-code solutions: 

	Provide the project files, templates, or configurations used to build the web scraping application.

	Include any necessary instructions or documentation to set up and run the no-code solution.

3.	Documentation: 

o	Detailed documentation should be provided, including: 

	Installation and setup instructions for the web scraping application.

	User guides and tutorials on how to use and maintain the application.

	Explanations of the data extraction rules, algorithms, and any custom logic implemented.

	API documentation, if applicable, for integrating the web scraping application with other systems.

4.	Data Export Files: 

o	The web scraping application should generate data export files in the agreed-upon format (e.g., CSV, JSON) that are compatible with our existing event management application.

o	The export files should contain the extracted data, structured and formatted according to the specified requirements.

5.	Training and Support: 

o	Provide training sessions or materials to familiarize our team with the web scraping application and its usage.

o	Offer support and assistance during the initial setup and integration process.

o	Be available for a specified period (e.g., 30 days) after the project completion to address any issues or provide additional guidance.

6.	Intellectual Property Rights: 

o	For custom development: 

	Transfer the intellectual property rights of the developed web scraping application to our company upon project completion.

	Ensure that the application is free from any third-party licenses or dependencies that may restrict our usage rights.

o	For no-code solutions: 

	Provide clear documentation on the usage rights and any limitations associated with the chosen no-code platform.

	Ensure that we have the necessary permissions and licenses to use the web scraping application built with the no-code tool.

7.	Maintenance and Support Plan (Optional): 

o	If offered, include a maintenance and support plan that covers bug fixes, updates, and enhancements to the web scraping application for a specified period after the project completion.

o	Detail the scope, response times, and pricing of the maintenance and support services.

Please note that the specific deliverables may vary slightly depending on the chosen approach (custom development or no-code) and the specific requirements of the project.

The selected developer or no-code solution expert should work closely with our team to ensure that the delivered web scraping application meets our expectations and is seamlessly integrated with our existing event management system.

Evaluation Criteria Proposals will be evaluated based on the following criteria:

1.	Relevant experience and expertise in web scraping and data extraction.

2.	Feasibility and suitability of the proposed approach (custom development or no-code) for the project requirements.

3.	Estimated timeline and cost for the proposed approach.

4.	Clarity and completeness of the proposal.

Please submit your proposal, including the requested information based on your preferred approach (custom development or no-code), along with any additional details or considerations you believe are relevant to this project.

We are open to both custom development and no-code solutions and will evaluate proposals based on their merits and alignment with our budget and project goals.

title: Web App for Parsing Bank Statements - Upwork
description:
Project Overview

We are in the business of merchant cash advance and require a web application to automate the parsing of bank statements in PDF format. The application should extract specific data points and generate reports that will aid in our financial analysis and decision-making processes.

Objectives

The main objective of this project is to develop a web application that can:

	1.	Parse bank statements in PDF format.

	2.	Extract and report on specific data points.

	3.	Generate a detailed returns report.

	4.	Calculate true revenue by considering various financial factors.

Key Features and Requirements

1. PDF Parsing

	•	The application should be able to upload and parse bank statements in PDF format.

	•	Use a reliable PDF parsing library or tool to extract data accurately.

2. Data Extraction

	•	Fundings

	•	Extract the date of deposit, amount, and lender name for any fundings.

	•	Daily/Weekly Pulls

	•	Identify and list daily/weekly pull amounts and lender names.

	•	Notify of any changes in payment amounts (increases or decreases).

	•	NSFs/Stopped Payments

	•	Identify and report any Non-Sufficient Funds (NSFs) or stopped payments.

	•	Revenue

	•	Calculate and display the average daily balance, highest daily balance, and lowest daily balance.

	•	Calculate ‘true revenue’ as revenue minus any transfers.

3. Returns Report

	•	Generate a comprehensive report displaying:

	•	Fundings

	•	Daily/Weekly Pulls

	•	NSFs/Stopped Payments

	•	Revenue metrics (average, highest, lowest daily balance)

	•	True revenue

Technical Requirements

	•	Backend: Preferably Python for the parsing and data extraction.

	•	Frontend: A user-friendly interface for uploading PDFs and viewing reports.

	•	Database: To store parsed data for future reference and analysis.

	•	Libraries/Tools: Utilize libraries such as PyPDF2 or PDFMiner for PDF parsing, and Pandas for data manipulation and calculations.

Resources

Refer to this guide for detailed steps on creating a bank statement parser with Python: Creating a Bank Statement Parser with Python.

Deliverables

	1.	A fully functional web application.

	2.	Source code with documentation.

	3.	User manual or guide for using the application.

	4.	Initial setup and deployment support.

Budget

Please provide a detailed quotation based on the project scope and deliverables.
skills: Python,     Java,     PDF

title: Python developer - Full stack - Upwork
description:
Job Title:  Python developer

Description:

We are looking for a python developer to join our team in developing a ai trading bot

You need to be an expert with python as well as familiar with cryptocurrency and crypto exchange api, WebSocket, k-lines. We will mostly be using Kucoin as api, WebSocket.

This job is for a long term position since we have a lot of project and each project will be paid minimum around 100$+

We will run a trial contract of 5$ at first to confirm your python skills, your knowledge, your efficiently, how clean you make your coding,etc.

Here is the summary for this trial contract

The goal of this bot is to engage in day trading with leverage, with a focus on managing risk through well-defined stop-loss and take-profit strategies. The bot aims to:

Open trades with a stop-loss set at approximately 0.5% in the opposite direction of the trade.

Set take-profit levels at around 1.5%.

This risk management strategy ensures that even if three trades hit the stop-loss, a single winning trade will recover the losses, maintaining overall profitability.

This strategy is designed to balance risk and reward effectively, aiming for a win ratio that allows the bot to remain profitable even with a series of losses.

Sample Plan

Data Collection from Futures Market (Completed)

- Objective: Ensure continuous real-time data fetching from the futures market.

- Method: Maintain an active WebSocket connection to collect and store incoming data for analysis.

Real-time Signal Generation

- Objective: Generate trading signals in real-time using the live data.

- Method: Implement signal generation logic to operate on real-time data as it is received, identifying trading signals based on technical indicators and patterns.

Simulated Trade Execution (backtest.py)

- Objective: Create a simulated trading environment to execute trades with fake money based on generated signals.

- Method:

- Track trades, including entry and exit points, stop-loss, and take-profit levels.

- Ensure that only one trade can be open at a time for both BTC and ETH. If the bot opens a long position on BTC, it cannot open another trade for BTC or ETH until the current trade is closed.

- This feature should already be implemented in the current backtest.py script.

Performance Monitoring (backtest.py)

- Objective: Continuously monitor the bot’s performance over a 5-day period.

- Method: Collect metrics such as profit/loss, win rate, number of trades executed, and other relevant statistics.

The bot runs data_collection_futures.py continuously to fetch real-time data from the futures market.

The bot runs real_time_signal_generation.py continuously to generate trading signals based on the real-time data it receives.

The bot runs backtest.py continuously to read the signals and execute simulated trades, tracking their outcomes.

This integrated approach ensures that the bot can trade effectively, using real-time data to generate signals and execute trades while continuously monitoring performance.
skills: AI Bot,     AI App Development,     AI Model Integration,     Python,     Cryptocurrency,     API,     RESTful API

title: Data Scientist/Analyst for Optimizing Second-Hand Fashion Pricing Strategy - Upwork
description:
Description:

We are a startup specializing in second-hand fashion for women, aiming to optimize our pricing strategy for maximum sales. We seek a skilled Data Scientist/Analyst to analyze our sales data and build a predictive model to set the optimal starting price (GradeA) for our pieces.

Objectives:

- Data Analysis: Conduct an exploratory data analysis (EDA) to understand the current pricing and sales trends.

- Model Building: Develop a predictive model to estimate the probability of sale at different price points.

- Price Optimization: Use the model to suggest the optimal starting price (GradeA) that maximizes the likelihood of sale.

- Database Integration: Ensure all data and results are stored in a MySQL database for easy querying.

Data Attributes:

- Brand

- Category (e.g., top, blouse, t-shirt)

- Color

- Size

- Season (summer/winter/no season)

- Grade (GradeA, GradeB, etc.)

- Price

- Sold (Yes/No)

Deliverables:

- EDA Report: Visualizations and insights from the data analysis.

- Predictive Model: A machine learning model (preferably built in Python) with detailed documentation.

- Optimized Pricing Recommendations: A strategy for setting the GradeA price based on the model’s 

predictions.

- Database Setup: All data and model outputs should be accessible via a MySQL database.

Requirements:

- Proven experience in data science and statistical analysis.

- Proficiency in Python (Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-Learn) or R.

- Experience with machine learning models such as logistic regression, Random Forests, or Gradient Boosting Machines.

- Strong SQL skills and experience with MySQL.

- Ability to communicate findings and recommendations clearly.

- Experience in retail or fashion industry is a plus.

How to Apply. Please provide:

- A brief overview of your experience relevant to this project.

- Examples of similar projects you have completed.

- Your proposed approach for this project.

- An estimated timeline and budget.

title: Extracting Features From News Data - OpenAI API, PostgreSql - Upwork
description:
This project focuses on extracting specific AI-related features from news articles and storing the parsed information in a PostgreSQL database. The articles are related to specific companies, identified by their company name and stock symbol. The extracted features include AI R&D spending, AI patents, AI research publications, AI product announcements, AI infrastructure investment, and AI talent.

Project Overview

The main objective of this project is to process news articles, extract relevant AI-related information, and store the parsed data in the appropriate database tables. The key components of the project are:

1) News articles database table (news_articles):

-Contains metadata such as id, url, date, and symbol (used to identify the company).

-Stores the full text of the article in the full_text column.

-Includes a llm_full_text_summary column to store a summary of the article generated by a language model.

2.) AI feature extraction:

-Utilizes OpenAI's ChatCompletion API to extract information related to specific AI categories.

-Parses the API response to identify relevant data points.

-Determines the type of information (quarterly, annual, or event-specific) and associates it with the corresponding company.

3.) Database integration:

-Inserts the extracted AI feature data into the respective database tables:

--ai_rd_spending: AI R&D spending data

--ai_patents: AI patent data

--ai_research_publications: AI research publication data

--ai_product_announcements: AI product announcement data

--ai_infrastructure_investment: AI infrastructure investment data

--ai_talent: AI talent data

Each table includes columns for the company symbol, data type (quarterly, annual, event-specific), year, quarter, event date, category, value, URL, and date.

4.) Database Schema

The project utilizes a PostgreSQL database with the following tables:

--news_articles: Stores the news articles and their metadata.

--ai_rd_spending: Stores AI R&D spending data.

--ai_patents: Stores AI patent data.

--ai_research_publications: Stores AI research publication data.

--ai_product_announcements: Stores AI product announcement data.

--ai_infrastructure_investment: Stores AI infrastructure investment data.

--ai_talent: Stores AI talent data.

The database connection is established using psycopg2 and SQLAlchemy libraries.

Project Status and Future Enhancements

Currently, the project has the core business logic implemented, including the database schema, OpenAI ChatCompletion API integration, and basic data parsing. However, some areas need further development and refinement:

-Improve the parsing logic to accurately extract AI feature data from the ChatCompletion API responses.

-Ensure proper insertion of parsed data into the respective database tables.

-Handle edge cases and error scenarios gracefully.

This contract will only be completed and paid if the parsing of openAI response for the news articles correctly works and inserts the expected data into it's respective database tables. All the same libraries and coding structure as the current code must be used and only extending any existing logic to enhance the functionality from some of the bugs it currently gets.

title: MongoDB Optimization Expert Needed for Performance Enhancement - Upwork
description:
I have a server of c6a.xlarge type installed mongodb on EC2 in AWS and I provide service to my other servers in this with MongoDB installed with static IP. It works as a single instance.

I have been monitoring mongodb with Datadog for years. Even though there have been occasional problems for 3 years, I have managed to cope so far without a problem in general. Now I don't want to postpone some problems and I need an expert to solve them.

Problem 1) The issue I'm facing is that my EC2 server, which is 125 GB in size, is 90 GB full. However, when I log on to the server using SSH, I see that only 20 GB of that space is being utilized by the database. The server's size has been increased from its initial 50 GB to 85 GB, and now to 125 GB, but the database hasn't grown proportionately. I can't figure out why the SSD requires more space over time. Even though I suspect that logs and similar files may be the cause, I haven't been able to solve this problem.

Problem 2) With Datadog, I can see in real time what query comes to the db and there are two uncertain points when I look at my current load. There are 2 queries and it constitutes more than 75% of my mongodb traffic "blocked-resource" and "ismaster admin.$cmd". Video explanation: https://www.loom.com/share/84a3fe9cf92749eea52a684ae739283a

I want to understand and fix these queries.

Problem 3) As far as I control Datadog, we really have very little use, but why are we using between 50-70% of CPU of for a server with 8GB 4CPU, how can this be? Maybe datadog queries are misleading me and we need to install a different tool directly on the server and provide a different analysis.

I would like to check all of these and fix the situations by doing meets with me. Before you apply for the job, share with me what your work process will be, what permissions you will ask for, and if you will use a performance tracking tool and I can understand how the process will work and make my choice accordingly.

Thanks.

I hope this message finds you well. I need your assistance in performing a confirmatory factor analysis (CFA) on the SPQ-B questionnaire data. Below, I have outlined the necessary steps and models that need to be tested.

Project Overview

We are validating different factor models for the SPQ-B (Schizotypal Personality Questionnaire-Brief) based on previously established models. The data has been collected from 443 undergraduate students at the University of Barcelona.

Models to be Tested

Ferichou et al. (2017) - 3-Factor Model

Disorganized: i1, i3, i6, i10, i11, i13, i16, i19, i20

Interpersonal: i7, i8, i14, i15, i17, i18, i22

Cognitive/Perceptual: i2, i4, i5, i9, i12

Raine (1991) - Original 3-Factor Model

Positive (Cognitive-Perceptual): i2, i4, i5, i7, i9, i10, i12, i14, i16, i17

Negative (Interpersonal): i11, i15, i18, i20, i21, i22

Disorganized: i1, i3, i6, i8, i13, i19

Stefanis et al. - 4-Factor Model

Cognitive-Perceptual: i2, i4, i5, i9, i12

Paranoia: i2, i4, i5, i9, i12

Interpersonal: i11, i15, i18, i20, i21, i2

Disorganization: i3, i6, i8, i13, i19

title: Freelance Developer Needed for Advanced RAG and Weaviate Implementation - Upwork
description:
We are seeking a highly skilled freelance developer to spearhead the development of a cutting-edge retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) system using Verba and Weaviate. This project involves implementing a dynamic, API-driven architecture capable of handling multiple Weaviate databases for distinct entities and integrating advanced text and PDF file ingestion.

Key Responsibilities:

- RAG Implementation: Develop a RAG system using Verba and Weaviate as shown in this tutorial https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IiNDCPwmqF8 . The system should be able to handle complex queries and integrate seamlessly with AI models.

- Database Management: Set up and manage multiple Weaviate databases for different clients (e.g., Company1, Company2). Implement mechanisms to switch between databases as needed. Ability to inject large PDF and Text files. 

- Data Ingestion and Filtering: Design an ingestion filter that processes documents by converting specific keywords into keys during ingestion. Implement a system where these keys are converted back to the original text in the output, managing a separate database for key-to-original text mappings.

- GPU Integration: Install and optimize RAG and Weaviate on a GPU infrastructure. Ensure compatibility with the ChatGPT API or a custom model from Hugging Face. Full documentation on installation and utilization required. 

- API Development: Develop a robust API for querying the system and ingesting data with various parameters such as data chunking. Ensure the API supports complex query functionalities and efficient response handling.

Position: Long-term Contract (30-40 hours/week)

Hourly Rate: $50-70 (depending on experience)

Work Setting: Start-up/small development team with developers and domain experts aiming to bring a product to market. If you want to develop cutting edge technology this position is for you. This job is the ultimate tech nerd’s dream.

Overview:

Imagine a system that can accept any document/file/image, understand it, extract semantic details and features, and create dynamic visuals. That's our system.

We are seeking a full stack developer/DevOps/Data engineer who is ready to dive into the project and wear many hats.

Product Background:

Our project leverages large language models (LLMs) to process various data types (payment transactions, documents, payment checks, GIS) and create analytics. Interactive visuals are generated based on these analytics. Users can use chatbots (LLMs) to query and interact with the data. The system aims to be self-consistent and validate dynamic LLM outputs.

OpenAI models

Multi-cloud environment (AWS S3, Google Recognize, Azure GPT4V + OCR enhancements)

Experience with cloud services and deploying scalable systems.

Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail.

Past experience formalizing environments for a SaaS or related software with users.

You will join a small, talented group of seven developers from around the world with varying skill sets. As we approach our launch within the next month, your role will be critical in ensuring our SaaS is up and running at scale. Initially, the scale needed is low (likely less than 100 users in the first three months) but will grow to a few thousand users.

title: VDM Specification Language Expert - Upwork
description:
We are looking for a highly skilled freelancer with expertise in VDM specification language. The ideal candidate should have a strong background in formal specification methods and experience in developing models using VDM. The project involves creating detailed specifications for a complex software system. The freelancer will be responsible for analyzing requirements, designing and documenting formal models, and ensuring compliance with industry standards. Strong problem-solving and communication skills are essential for this role. 

Consider a robot moving across a room (treated like a 6 by 6 grid) in order to exit

from a door. The robot always starts at position 1,1. The robot may move left, right,

up and down by one grid square at a time. When the robot reaches the door it may

exit and another robot immediately enters the room in position 1,1.

Software to monitor the robot is to be developed. Initial analysis of the software

has produced the following UML diagram:

We will provide you with the RobotMonitor.rtf specification and you must complete the VDM-SL model of this system, using VDMTools to ensure it is free of syntax and type errors.

RobotMonitor

row: Integer

col: Integer

MoveRight()

MoveLeft()

MoveUp()

MoveDown()

GetRow( ): Integer

GetCol( ) : Integer

Exit( )

Task B

Validating and Verifying Formal Models

Use VDMTools to thoroughly test the RobotMonitor.rtf model you

produced in task A - correcting any logical errors you may find. We will then provide you a sampleTestDocumentation.pdf file to illustrate how you can document your testing.

A RobotMonitor class has been discussed in task A and B above. You should have

a formal VDM-SL model of this class from task A and this model will have been

thoroughly tested in task B. We will then provide the following files:

1. RobotMonitor.java

2. Move.java

3. VDMException.java

4. RobotMonitorGUI.java

5. RunRobotGUI.java

6. RunRobotText.java

The RobotMonitor.java file is an incomplete Java implementation of the

RobotMonitor model discussed above. Complete the implementation of this

RobotMonitor.java class, being sure to use defensive programming techniques.

You can test this class by running it alongside the additional classes provided. If

you are using a desktop Java IDE (such as NetBeans or eclipse) you can use the

GUI interface to test your RobotMonitor.java class by running the

RunRobotMonitorGUI.java file. 

If you do not have access to a Java IDE such as NetBeans, you may use a web-based Java tool (such as JDoodle). Web-based Java tools such as JDoodle cannot

run programs with a GUI interface, so to test your RobotMonitor.java class use

the text based tester fie RunRobotMonitorText.java.

Submit the following files

• your completed RobotMonitor.rtf VDM specification file

• your RobotMonitor testing documentation

• your updated test data file

• your completed RobotMonitor.java class file.

   

Write a report with the following title:

“Formal Methods for Computer Science Professionals”.

The report should reflect on the legal, social, ethical and professional reasons for

Computer Science Professionals to use formal methods to develop high integrity

software and make reference to your RobotMonitor project to identify how formal

methods were used to improve the quality of the final software.

Your report should include references that are presented in Harvard referencing

style.

   Required Skills:

   - Proficiency in VDM specification language

   - Experience in formal specification methods

   - Strong analytical and problem-solving skills

   - Excellent communication and documentation skills

   

   Preferred Skills:

   - Knowledge of software engineering principles

   - Experience in software modeling and verification

   

   If you have a deep understanding of VDM specification language and are passionate about formal specification methods, we would love to hear from you.
skills: Web Development,     JavaScript,     PHP,     English,     Python

title: AI Web Application Developer - Upwork
description:
We are seeking a skilled AI web application developer to create a web application that connects to a stock broker for data, performs analysis, and provides advice to the user. 

I am looking to have a proof-of-concept created of a platform that combines a few elements I am already doing manually (using various platforms to do so) to create an easy to use tool to help me manage my stock portfolio.  What the tool should be able to do in its most basic form:

1) Connect to my broker to get data about my portfolio.  What positions are owned, buy price, date, profit/loss, etc

2) Feed that data into the ChatGPT AI model

3) Get management advice for each position based on some guiding criteria (risk tolerance, looking to maximize profit or minimize risk, capital willing to risk, etc).  I can provide some prompt guidance and training so that the AI is doing the correct thing

4) Get pricing data for the strategies suggested.  The AI may suggest, for example, to buy a put at certain strike.  We need to be able to get the price of that put option to understand the profit/loss scenarios.

5) a simple streamlined outline of each suggested strategy for each position.  The AI, in my manual testing, often gives options so would be good to outline these very simply

6) Include max profit / max loss calculations for each strategy suggested

7) some ability to ask questions about the strategies and or ask for changes/tweaks

This is mostly connecting API's and doing math against the data retrieved and then providing the results in an easy to use format.

 

Technical Experience Requirements:

- ChatGPT API

- stock broker API connection (get requests)

- Web application development

- Data management in cloud

Right now this is just for my use.  But I do want the ability to have it be scalable so if I want to add users, make it a full product, etc that I can do that without having to redo everything.

title: Building an AI-Powered Virtual Interview Platform - Upwork
description:
Dear Freelancer,

I hope this message finds you well. I am reaching out to discuss an exciting project opportunity and to see if you would be interested in collaborating with us.

Our vision is to create an innovative, AI-driven virtual interview platform that empowers job seekers to improve their interview skills and connects employers with top talent. We believe that this platform has the potential to revolutionize the job search and hiring process.

A key differentiator of our platform is the integration of advanced AI technology. We have partnered with Claude, a state-of-the-art AI assistant developed by Anthropic. Claude's capabilities in natural language processing, machine learning, and data analysis will be instrumental in powering the core functionalities of our platform.

For the initial phase of the project, we are focusing on developing the following features:

Virtual Interview Simulator:

Job seekers can participate in realistic, AI-generated mock interviews tailored to their job preferences.

Claude will analyze the candidate's performance and provide detailed feedback and recommendations for improvement.

Interview data for top-performing candidates will be stored in a searchable database.

Comprehensive Candidate Evaluation:

Online Assessments: Candidates will complete a series of online tests to assess their skills, knowledge, and aptitude relevant to their desired job roles. Claude will analyze the test results and generate insights into the candidate's strengths and areas for improvement.

Facial Analysis during Video Interviews: We will utilize advanced facial recognition and analysis techniques to evaluate the candidate's facial expressions, eye movements, and overall demeanor during the virtual interviews. This data will be processed by Claude to provide an in-depth understanding of the candidate's confidence, engagement, and communication skills.

Behavioral and Psychological Insights: Claude will analyze the candidate's responses, language patterns, and behavioral cues to assess their personality traits, emotional intelligence, and potential fit within specific job roles and company cultures.

Employer Access to Talent Pool:

Companies can subscribe to the platform to access the database of pre-vetted, high-performing candidates.

They can search for candidates based on specific criteria and view their comprehensive evaluation reports, including interview performance, assessment results, and behavioral insights.

This will allow employers to make data-driven hiring decisions and identify the most suitable candidates for their organization.

From a technical perspective, we envision the following key components:

Interactive web platform with user dashboards for job seekers and employers

Integration of Claude's AI capabilities for interview question generation, candidate performance analysis, and insights

Secure video interview interface with real-time facial analysis and language processing powered by Claude

Scalable database to store user profiles, assessment results, interview data, and evaluation reports

Messaging and notification system for communication between candidates and employers

We are looking for a skilled freelance developer to help us bring this vision to life. Your role would be to work closely with our team to design and develop the platform, integrate Claude's AI components seamlessly, and ensure a smooth user experience.

If this opportunity aligns with your expertise and interests, we would be delighted to discuss further details and explore how we can collaborate effectively. Please let me know if you have any questions or if you would like to schedule a call to discuss the project in more depth.

Thank you for considering this opportunity. I look forward to the possibility of working together to create a truly innovative and impactful platform.

Best regards,

Farhan

title: Kubernetes(ARGO Template Expert) - Upwork
description: I need someone to create an Argo workflow template in YAML format to call several SQL stored procedures, both in parallel and sequentially. The DB user credentials should be parsed as a secret in the template. The first step is to schedule a check to see if it's the end of the day (considering the time of day, timezone, and day of the week). If the time is correct, proceed to the second step; otherwise, stop. The second step involves stopping services by calling a SQL stored procedure. If services are stopped successfully, continue; otherwise, fail. The third step is to take a backup by calling a SQL stored procedure on two SQL servers in parallel. If the stored procedure completes successfully, continue; otherwise, fail. The fourth step is to perform indexing by calling a SQL stored procedure on two SQL servers in parallel. If indexing completes successfully, continue; otherwise, fail. The fifth step is to start services by calling a SQL stored procedure. If services start successfully, end the process; otherwise, fail. This template should be parameterized to allow the addition of actual stored procedure names, timezone format, etc

title: Database Administrator or Back-end Developer Required for Magento 2 - Upwork
description:
Hi,

I am looking for a Magento 2 and a Database Administrator / Back-end Developer to complete the given below requirements:

Scenario: The store is based on Magento 2.4.6-p3 with all necessary server requirements such as Nginx 1.22, MariaDb 10.6, Varnish cache 7.3, php 8.1, Composer 2.2, Elasticsearch 8.5, MySQL 10.6, RabbitMQ 3.11, Redis 7, etc.

Here are the details of the products present in the database (TO BE IMPORTED BY YOU):

1. The product database size is 411 GB. There are no product attributes, or variables. Just simple products. You have to import the product database provided in SQL format in zipped file of 80GB. On decompress, you would have 411GB product database.

2. There are no product images

Magento Modules Installed and configured:

1. Amasty Elasticsearch: https://amasty.com/elasticsearch-for-magento-2.html

2. Amasty Google Speed Optimiser Pro: https://amasty.com/google-page-speed-optimizer-for-magento-2.html

3. Amasty Varnish Full Page Cache Warmer: https://amasty.com/full-page-cache-warmer-for-magento-2.html

Webserver access I would provide to you are given below. Currently, the website is hosted on Hetzner cloud and it has to be moved to the following server by you:

1. Web Server: Intel Core i7-8700, 6 cores / 12 threads @ 3.6 GHz, 64 GB DDR4 RAM, 1TB NVMe SSD (€35.70)

2. Application Server: AX41-NVMe, AMD Ryzen™ 5 3600, 4 cores / 8 threads @3 Ghz, 64 GB DDR4, 1TB NVMe SSD (€37.31)

3. Database Server: Intel Xeon W-2145, 256GB DDR4 RAM, 8 cores / 16 threads @ 3.6 GHz, 2 TB NVMe SSD (€88.70)

4. ElasticSearch: AMD Ryzen 9 5950X, 128GB DDR4 RAM, 16 cores / 32 threads @ 4.9 GHz, 2 TB NVMe SSD (€68.70)

5. Redis Cache & Varnish Cache Server: 8 cores / 16 threads, 64 GB DDR4 RAM and 2TB NVMe (€31.70)

6. Load Balancer: Hetzner Cloud Load Balancer

7. Hetzner Storage Box: 10 TB (€20)

Requirements:

1. Migrate the Magento 2 server from the Hetzner cloud to Hetzner dedicated server

2. Install necessary software and implement the following on their individual servers: Web Server, Application Server, Database Server, Elastic Search Server, Redis Cache, Varnish Cache and Load Balancer

3. Import the product database of 411 GB database. I will provide the database in SQL format.

4. Optimise the Elasticsearch and page load. We expect 200 concurrent users anytime throughout the day

5. Elasticsearch should index all the products and all the products should be searchable.

6. Optimize website performance. Current score on Google page speed insight is 47 on mobile and 83 on Desktop.

7. Product search result should be less than 3 seconds

8. Setup firewall on all the servers

9. Implement control panel so that it is easy to monitor all servers, backup and restore the server. Kindly suggest few open source ones.

10. Raid1 configuration to ensure that we have an exact replica of the hard drive on each server

11. Setup automatic backup of all the servers to Hetzner Storage Box

12. Provide backup of the entire server including the database at the end of the project

13. Compress the XML sitemap into “.xml.gz” format

Here is my advice, however, I am open to suggestions:

————————————

To optimize Elasticsearch and database performance for 100 concurrent users, you would have to implement the following strategies and techniques:

1. Index Optimization:

- Use appropriate index mapping types (e.g., keyword, text, long) for fields.

- Enable index compression and refresh intervals.

- Use index aliases for efficient querying.

2. Query Optimization:

- Use efficient query types (e.g., term, phrase, match) and avoid slow queries (e.g., regex, wildcard).

- Implement query filtering and caching.

- Use search templates for reusable queries.

3. Database Configuration:

- Adjust JVM heap size and garbage collection settings.

- Configure disk storage and I/O settings for optimal performance.

- Enable database monitoring and alerting.

4. Caching and Buffering:

- Implement caching layers (e.g., Varnish, Redis, Memcached) for frequent queries.

- Use buffer sizes and queue capacities to manage concurrent requests.

5. Monitoring and Analytics:

- Set up monitoring tools (e.g., Kibana, Grafana) for performance insights.

- Track query performance, latency, and error rates.

6. Load Balancing:

- Use load balancers (e.g., HAProxy, NGINX) to distribute incoming traffic.

7. Content Delivery Network (CDN):

- Consider using a CDN to offload static asset delivery and reduce database queries such as BunnyCDN.

————————————

Here's a high-level overview of the setup process for each component on a Hetzner dedicated server:

Database Server (MySQL/PostgreSQL)

1. Install the database server software (e.g., MySQL or PostgreSQL) using the package manager.

2. Configure the database server settings (e.g., database name, user credentials, storage engine) in the configuration files (e.g., my.cnf or postgresql.conf).

3. Create the necessary databases and users.

4. Configure any necessary database settings (e.g., character encoding, timezone).

5. Restart the database server service to apply changes.

Elastic Search Server

1. Install Elastic Search using the package manager or by downloading and installing the binaries.

2. Configure Elastic Search settings (e.g., cluster name, node name, index settings) in the configuration files (e.g., elasticsearch.yml).

3. Set up index mapping and analysis settings.

4. Configure any necessary plugins (e.g., Kibana, X-Pack).

5. Restart the Elastic Search service to apply changes.

Redis Cache

1. Install Redis using the package manager or by downloading and installing the binaries.

2. Configure Redis settings (e.g., port number, memory allocation, persistence) in the configuration files (e.g., redis.conf).

3. Set up any necessary Redis databases or instances.

4. Configure any necessary Redis settings (e.g., expiration policies, eviction policies).

5. Restart the Redis service to apply changes.

Varnish Cache

1. Install Varnish using the package manager or by downloading and installing the binaries.

2. Configure Varnish settings (e.g., port number, cache size, backend servers) in the configuration files (e.g., varnish.conf).

3. Set up any necessary Varnish caching rules or policies.

4. Configure any necessary Varnish settings (e.g., TTL, grace period).

5. Restart the Varnish service to apply changes.

Load Balancer (HAProxy/NGINX)

1. Install the load balancer software (e.g., HAProxy or NGINX) using the package manager.

2. Configure the load balancer settings (e.g., backend servers, balancing algorithm, health checks) in the configuration files (e.g., haproxy.cfg or nginx.conf).

3. Set up any necessary load balancing rules or policies.

4. Configure any necessary load balancer settings (e.g., session persistence, connection timeouts).

5. Restart the load balancer service to apply changes.

————————————

To ensure efficient page load times and high search performance, I would take the following measures:

1. Optimize Database Queries:

- Use efficient query algorithms and indexing.

- Limit database queries and use caching where possible.

- Optimize database server configuration and resources.

2. Implement Caching:

- Use Redis or Memcached for caching frequently accessed data.

- Implement page caching and fragment caching.

- Use CDN for static asset caching.

3. Optimize Elastic Search:

- Use appropriate indexing and mapping strategies.

- Optimize search queries and filtering.

- Use Elastic Search caching and warming.

4. Optimize Web Server Configuration:

- Use efficient web server software (e.g., Nginx).

- Configure optimal server settings (e.g., worker processes, connection timeouts).

- Enable HTTP/2 and SSL/TLS.

5. Enable Browser Caching:

- Set appropriate cache headers for static assets.

- Enable browser caching for frequently accessed resources.

6. Minify and Compress Files:

- Minify and compress JavaScript and CSS files.

- Use image compression tools (e.g., WebP).

7. Optimize Server Resources:

- Ensure sufficient CPU, memory, and disk resources.

- Monitor server performance and adjust resources as needed.

8. Use Load Balancing and Autoscaling:

- Distribute traffic across multiple servers.

- Scale servers based on traffic demand.

9. Monitor Performance:

- Use tools like New Relic, Datadog, or Prometheus to monitor performance.

- Track page load times, search performance, and server resources.

Here are some open-source control panels for server monitoring, backup management, and restoration: I NEED YOUR SUGGESTION ON THIS.

1. Webmin: A web-based interface for system administration, including monitoring, backup, and restoration.

2. Zabbix: A comprehensive monitoring tool for servers, networks, and applications.

3. Bareos (Backup Archiving Recovery Open Sourced): A backup and archiving solution with a web-based interface.

4. Duplicati: A backup client that supports various storage providers, including local disks and cloud services.

5. Areca Backup: A Java-based backup solution with a web interface and support for various storage devices.

6.	Bacula

For RAID configuration and weekly automatic backups, you can follow these general steps:

RAID Configuration:

1. Install the necessary RAID software (e.g., mdadm for Linux).

2. Configure the RAID array using the software (e.g., create a RAID 1 or 5 array).

3. Monitor the RAID array for errors and alerts.

Weekly Automatic Backups:

1. Install the backup software (e.g., Bareos, Duplicati, or Areca Backup).

2. Configure the backup job to run weekly, using a scheduler like cron (for Linux).

3. Set the backup source to the desired data (e.g., /home, /var, or specific directories).

4. Choose the backup destination (e.g., local disk, network share, or cloud storage).

5. Configure retention policies and backup verification options.

6. Monitor backup logs and alerts for errors or issues.

Some specific configuration examples:

- Webmin: Create a backup job in the "System" then "Backup" module, selecting the desired directories and destination.

- Bareos: Create a backup job in the "Jobs" tab, specifying the source and destination, and scheduling it using the "Schedule" tab.

- Duplicati: Create a backup job in the "Backup" tab, selecting the source and destination, and scheduling it using the "Schedules" tab.

Timelines: 2 - 3 weeks

Thanks!

title: Developer Needed for CSV to JSON Transformation and High-Volume Data Serving - Upwork
description:
We are seeking an experienced developer to help us create a serverless application within our AWS environment. The goal of this project is to periodically retrieve a CSV file from a URL, store it in S3, transform its content into a JSON feed, and efficiently serve individual objects from this feed via a query string. The response should be cached to handle high-volume traffic.

Project Requirements:

1. Retrieve CSV File:

   - Periodically download a CSV file from a specified URL.

   - Store the downloaded CSV file in an S3 bucket.

2. Transform CSV to JSON:

   - Parse the CSV content and transform it into a JSON format.

   - Each row in the CSV should be converted to a JSON object with an added unique identifier (`id`).

3. Serve JSON Data:

   - Create a function to retrieve a specific object from the JSON array based on a query string parameter (e.g., `?id=3`).

   - If no matching object is found, the function should return a random object from the array.

4. Cache Responses:

   - Implement caching for the responses to ensure the solution can handle high-volume HTTP traffic.

   - The cache should be invalidated and updated whenever the CSV file is re-downloaded and processed.

Technical Requirements:

- The solution should be built using AWS services, ideally leveraging serverless technologies such as AWS Lambda, API Gateway, and S3.

- The application should be designed for scalability and efficiency, ensuring minimal latency for data retrieval.

- Proper error handling and logging should be implemented for monitoring and troubleshooting purposes.

Deliverables:

- A fully functional serverless application deployed in our AWS environment.

- Source code with clear documentation.

- Configuration and deployment instructions.

- A brief test plan to verify the functionality of the application.

Skills Required:

- Proficiency in AWS services (Lambda, S3, API Gateway, etc.)

- Experience with serverless application development

- Strong understanding of JSON and CSV data formats

- Expertise in caching strategies for high-volume traffic

If you have experience in building scalable, serverless applications and can meet the above requirements, we would love to hear from you. Please provide examples of similar projects you have completed along with your proposal.

title: News scraping and comparison application development - Upwork
description:
We are looking for a skilled developer to create an application/software that can scrape news articles and compare them with domestic news outlets. 

Example, Reuters and Bloomberg publish around 40k articles each day. Local media like Nos.nl and Nu.nl (The Netherlands) only publish around 2k. This means a lot of news is not published in the Netherlands and not accessible without paying e.g. Reuters and Bloomberg. The idea is to create an application that compares the articles, removes articles that have already been published in the Netherlands, removes articles like columns and documentaries and thus leaves 'the news from yesterday'. These articles then need to be uploaded to a website where they can be viewed. 

The goal is to generate a comprehensive news report from the previous day with articles that local news outlets have missed. The application should have the following capabilities:

- Efficiently scrape news articles from various sources

- Compare the scraped articles with domestic news outlets

- Identify and eliminate duplicate articles

- Categorize the articles based on their topic

- Generate a consolidated news report for the previous day

Skills needed:

- Web scraping

- Data comparison and analysis

- Article categorization

- Report generation

This is a medium-sized project and is expected to take around 1 to 3 months to complete. We are looking for an intermediate-level developer with experience in developing similar applications. We first want to get an idea of costs and whether it is possible before we continue with the project.

title: Software developer to build IDE for data engineering and analysis - Upwork
description:
I'm looking for a software engineer for part-time to work on an Integrated Development Environment specifically designed for SQL data analysis and data engineering.

PROJECT BACKGROUND

The IDE will leverage computational tree analysis, machine learning, and large language models to analyse the code base and data model to extract business logic and reason about the data. This will enhance code completion, error detection, and automate many workflows.

There are 5 million SQL developers worldwide. They are both critical for businesses especially large corporations, but also are highly inefficient. The market potential is huge.

These developers create data pipelines that transform operational data (e.g. transactions from finance and sales systems) into high-level dashboards critical for executive decision making (e.g. profitability by product or customer).

Their inefficiency is caused by the lack of the right tools. Functionality of SQL editor does not go far beyond basic syntax checking and column names autocompletion. Compare this with software engineers who enjoy VSCode and IntelliJ and GitHub Copilot.

EXAMPLE OF A FEATURE

Example of a feature

One of the huge issues is business logic inconsistency. In a toy example, part of a team of 1,000 business intelligence analysts in some large bank would define a large client as revenue above $4 mln, while other part as revenue above $5 mln. This creates inconsistent reporting and multiple errors. Alternatively, they could have different grouping of the regions, filter out different types deals or products, and so on.

Solution is for the IDE to analyse the query analyst writes. If there is a code snippet, that looks similar but not exact to others in the code base, the IDE would highlight this as a potential error. Then it'd find the example that looks like a reliable version (say revenue above $5 mln is used in the production pipelines or by the majority of users), and suggest this as an alternative.
skills: Python,     SQL,     Node.js,     JavaScript
