title: Graphic designer to help us visualize our technology - Upwork
description:
We are a rapidly growing tech startup specializing in a SaaS analytics platform tailored for enterprises like telecom operators, utilities, and energy companies. Our platform facilitates an end-to-end data valorization journey, encompassing data acquisition, cataloging, workflows, automations, and visualization for decision support.

Here is my LinkedIn profile so you can learn more about me and our startup:

https://www.linkedin.com/in/ahmedghadani/

We're seeking an experienced Graphic Designer who can visually articulate complex concepts into clear and engaging illustrations. The ideal candidate will transform our ideas into marketing and sales materials that effectively communicate the sophistication and value of our platform to a high-level audience.

Responsibilities:

*Design and develop illustrations that represent complex data flows and functionalities of our SaaS platform.

*Create an innovative concept illustration of our platform visualized as a "data cube," where each slice represents a different module (Connector, Observatory, Workflows, Visualization), and each block within that slice depicts a specific function of the module.

*Ensure designs are visually appealing and communicate the premium and sophisticated nature of our technology in a futuristic style.

*Collaborate closely with our marketing and product teams to ensure that the illustrations align with our branding and product messaging.

*Deliver high-quality, high-resolution images suitable for both digital and print media.

Requirements:

*Proven graphic design experience with a strong portfolio of work in tech and/or data analytics.

*Expertise in digital illustration tools such as Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop, or similar.

*Ability to interpret complex technical and business concepts and translate them into accessible visual formats.

*Excellent communication and collaboration skills to effectively work with cross-functional teams.

*Creative thinker with attention to detail and a passion for delivering engaging and impactful visual content.

Project Description:

For the initial project, you will design a detailed illustration of our analytics platform conceptualized as a sophisticated "data cube." This cube should be presented in a futuristic style, highlighting the modularity of our system where each "slice" of the cube represents a different module of our platform, and each block within the slice details a function of that module.

The final illustration should not only serve as a compelling visual aid for our sales and marketing efforts but also showcase your ability to handle complex design challenges and contribute to our ongoing projects.

Submission Requirements:

*Submit a brief outline of your approach to designing the "data cube" concept.

*Include a link to your portfolio showcasing relevant work.

*Provide an estimate of the time and budget required for completing the initial illustration.

I will be using this initial project as a way to evaluate working with the candidates. This role requires someone who is innovative, detail-oriented, and capable of delivering extraordinary visual content that aligns with our vision of transforming how enterprises interact with data. If you are passionate about creating visuals that simplify complex ideas and elevate brand perception, we would love to hear from you.

Here is more detailed description about each module and what does it do:

1. Connector Module

Description:

The Connector Module serves as the gateway to your data, acting as the critical first step in the data valorisation journey. This module functions as an integration and API gateway, allowing for the seamless incorporation of various data sources into our analytics platform. Its design ensures that no data, regardless of its origin or format, is beyond reach.

Features:

Easy-to-Use Integration Wizard: The Connector Module features an intuitive wizard that guides users through the process of adding and integrating data sources. This wizard simplifies what can often be a complex set of tasks, making data integration accessible even to users with minimal technical expertise.

Wide Range of Supported Protocols: Whether dealing with older legacy systems that operate on traditional FTP or sFTP protocols, or modern databases and APIs, the Connector Module is equipped to handle all. It also supports direct connections to edge devices and edge systems via protocols like MQTT, making it incredibly versatile.

High Compatibility: The module is designed to work seamlessly with both legacy systems and the latest data source technologies. This ensures that organisations do not have to overhaul their existing data infrastructures to benefit from our platform, but can instead enhance their current systems with powerful new data analytics capabilities.

Secure Data Handling: With security at the forefront, the Connector Module ensures that all data integrations are performed in a secure and compliant manner, safeguarding your data from acquisition to insight.

This Connector Module is not just about collecting data; it’s about setting the stage for powerful insights that drive decision-making, all while maintaining a user-friendly and secure environment for data integration.

2. Observatory Module

Description:

The Observatory Module is a core component of our SaaS analytics platform, designed to enhance the usability and accessibility of data. It systematically organises and catalogues data, transforming a diverse array of data streams into a structured and easily navigable format. This module is essential for businesses that aim to leverage their data efficiently and effectively, as it provides a clear and coherent overview of all available data resources.

Features:

Data Catalog Creation: This feature is the heart of the Observatory Module. It automatically generates a detailed data catalogue that includes metadata and indexing for every dataset integrated into the platform. This catalogue serves as a central repository where data from various sources is not only stored but also meticulously described and classified, making it straightforward for users to find and understand the data they need.

Customizable Grouping of Data: Users can group data into datasets based on relevance, project, source, or any other criteria that suits their operational needs. This customizable grouping allows for enhanced data management and helps users focus on the data that is most relevant to their specific analytics tasks.

Subscription Options for Datasets: The Observatory Module offers flexible subscription options that allow users to access datasets as needed. This includes both internal data specific to the organisation and third-party data that can be integrated for enriched analysis. Subscriptions can be managed and adjusted according to the changing needs of the business, ensuring that users always have access to the most relevant and current data.

Enhanced Data Discoverability: With advanced search functionalities and intuitive navigation, the Observatory Module makes it easy for users to discover and access the data they need without unnecessary delays. This feature is especially valuable in complex environments where the volume and variety of data can be overwhelming.

Security and Compliance: Ensuring the integrity and security of data, the Observatory Module incorporates robust security measures that comply with industry standards. This protects data at rest and in transit, providing organisations with the confidence that their information is secure while facilitating compliance with data protection regulations.

The Observatory Module not only simplifies data management but also empowers organisations to harness their data's full potential, ensuring that valuable insights are never more than a few clicks away.

3. Workflows Module

Description:

The Workflows Module is a dynamic component of our SaaS analytics platform, designed to empower users to perform sophisticated data processing and analysis within a low-code/no-code environment. This module facilitates seamless data manipulation, allowing users from various technical backgrounds to derive insights effectively and efficiently. It serves as a versatile tool for transforming raw data into actionable intelligence, accommodating both routine and complex analytical tasks.

Features:

Intuitive UI for Data Manipulation: Users can easily manipulate, process, and transform data using simple, user-friendly tools provided within the module. This interface is designed to lower the barrier to entry for performing data analytics, making it accessible for non-technical users while still powerful enough for experts.

Advanced Analytical Operations: The module supports advanced SQL operations, enabling users to perform complex queries and data aggregations effortlessly. It also includes tools for statistical modelling and machine learning, allowing for the automation of insight generation through sophisticated analytical techniques.

Custom Coding Capabilities: For users with programming skills, the Workflows Module offers the flexibility to write custom scripts in Python or R. This feature caters to data scientists and analysts who require the ability to implement highly customised analyses and algorithms directly within the platform.

Automation of Reports and Dashboards: Automation features within the module allow for the scheduled creation and updating of reports and dashboards. Users can set up workflows that automatically generate visual outputs, ensuring that stakeholders always have access to the latest insights without manual intervention.

Workflow Customisation and Sharing: Users can create customised workflows that can be saved and shared across the organisation. This promotes consistency in data processing and enables collaborative analysis, enhancing the collective data intelligence of the organisation.

Seamless Integration with Other Modules: The Workflows Module integrates seamlessly with the Connector and Observatory modules, providing a streamlined pipeline from data acquisition to analysis. This integration ensures that data flows smoothly across different stages of the valorization process, maximising efficiency and reducing the likelihood of errors.

The Workflows Module is pivotal in democratising data analysis, offering powerful tools that simplify complex processes and enable users at all levels of expertise to contribute to data-driven decision-making. This module is instrumental in turning the analytical capabilities of an organisation into a competitive advantage in the marketplace.

4. Visualisation Module

Description:

The Visualization Module is an integral part of our SaaS analytics platform, designed to enable dynamic and impactful data visualisation and reporting. This module transforms complex datasets into clear, insightful visual representations, making it easier for decision-makers to understand patterns, trends, and anomalies. With its advanced capabilities, the Visualization Module serves as a powerful tool for communicating data-driven insights across an organisation.

Features:

Dashboard Creator with Advanced Customization: Users can create custom dashboards using a variety of widgets and visualisation tools, including charts, graphs, and maps. The dashboard creator is designed for easy use but offers advanced customization options to meet the specific needs of different users and use cases.

Geospatial Visualisations: This feature allows users to incorporate maps and spatial data into their dashboards, providing a geographical context to the data. Geospatial visualisations are particularly useful for industries where location is a key factor, such as telecommunications, real estate, and logistics.

Configurable Alerts and Layers: The module offers the ability to set up configurable alerts that notify users of significant changes or anomalies in the data. Users can also create multiple layers within their visualisations to present data at different levels of detail, enhancing the depth and granularity of data analysis.

Export and Report Scheduling: To facilitate routine reporting and data sharing, the module includes functionalities for exporting visualisations in various formats and scheduling reports for automatic delivery via email or SMS. This ensures that all stakeholders receive timely updates and insights, even if they are not directly interacting with the platform.

Interactive Capabilities with Large Language Models (LLM): Integrating LLM technology, the Visualization Module allows users to interact with their data through natural language queries. This interaction can lead to deeper insights and simplifies the exploration of complex data sets, making analytics more accessible to non-expert users.

Integration with Workflows Module: The Visualization Module works seamlessly with the Workflows Module, allowing users to directly visualise the outcomes of their analytical workflows. This integration ensures that insights generated through complex processes are immediately visible and actionable.

The Visualization Module not only enhances the visual appeal of data but also boosts its utility by making complex information understandable at a glance. This module is crucial for organisations that rely on data to inform strategy, operational adjustments, and market positioning, providing a visual storytelling tool that is both powerful and user-friendly.

description:
### Job Title: Software Developer for BOSCH SENSORTECH BHI260AP Fitness Tracking Sensor

**Description:**

We are seeking a skilled software developer with experience in sensor data processing and machine learning to develop a fitness tracking system using the BOSCH SENSORTECH BHI260AP sensor. The project involves creating software that accurately counts repetitions for a variety of exercises by analyzing data from the sensor.

**Project Scope:**

1. **Sensor Configuration:** (DATA SUPPLIED BY HIRER)

   - Configure the BHI260AP sensor to capture accurate accelerometer and gyroscope data.

2. **Data Collection:**  (DATA SUPPLIED BY HIRER)

3. **Feature Extraction:**

   - Develop algorithms to process raw sensor data and extract relevant features such as accelerometer and gyroscope magnitude, time-domain features (mean, variance, energy), and frequency-domain features (FFT coefficients, power spectral density).

4. **Algorithm Development:**

   - Train machine learning models (e.g., CNN, RNN, Decision Trees, Random Forest) to accurately predict and count exercise repetitions.

   - Validate the model’s accuracy and make necessary adjustments to improve performance.

5. **Real-time Processing:**

   - Implement real-time data streaming from the sensor.

   - Develop software to apply the trained model for real-time exercise recognition and repetition counting.

6. **Validation and Calibration:**  (TO BE EXECUTED BY HIRER)

   - Perform validation exercises to ensure the accuracy of the algorithm.

   - Adjust and calibrate the model based on validation results.

**Qualifications:**

- Proven experience in developing software for sensor data processing and machine learning.

- Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, C++, or similar.

- Experience with machine learning frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn).

- Familiarity with accelerometer and gyroscope data processing.

- Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.

- Excellent communication skills and ability to work independently.

**Preferred Experience:**

- Experience with BOSCH SENSORTECH sensors, specifically the BHI260AP.

- Background in fitness tracking or similar applications.

- Experience in real-time data processing and embedded systems development.

**Deliverables:**

- Fully functional software that configures the BHI260AP sensor, collects and processes data, trains machine learning models, and provides real-time exercise recognition and repetition counting.

- Documentation of the software including setup instructions, usage guide, and code comments.

- Validation report demonstrating the accuracy and performance of the developed system.

title: Project Management Database Development - Upwork
description:
We are looking for a skilled database developer to create a comprehensive database system for managing our parts inventory. The main goal is to streamline the ordering process and track the logistics of the parts. 

We need to database to also assist with managing small projects within the company and on a particular job site, a small project will be established and all parts required either in stock or ordered will be allocated to the project, orders will then be tracked and their progress will be displayed in the project file. When the parts arrive onsite, this will also be displayed within the project file and the location where they are stored.

The database will have to have user management abilites, e.g employees will need to sign in to create an account, there will also be different levels of user access.

I believe that the quickest way to set up an inventory, is to scan the suppliers bar code for a part, but then marry that barcode, to a barcode that we develop, this will result in the same format for all of the parts we have on file and not have to continuously cater for many different suppliers barcodes. We may want to hae our barcode located at different locations around the site to be scanned, it will be hard to maintain if we use a different format for each supplier / product. 

The suppliers will be scanned once and this will be referenced next time we scan the same product, but it will be the barcode with our format that will be displayed.

The customers barcode is still essential, as the database needs to be able store our suppliers products catalogue, this will help with ordering new and or replacement parts.

We need to be able to enter many suppliers catalogue with the suppliers barcode, all the different suppliers barcodes will be referenced to a barcode that we generate.

A full scalable asset history needs to be available, we need to be able to enter details of machinery and other assets etc. This needs to be capable of storing ongoing data entry for each machine / asset.

We need search engines, we need to be able to search a prjoject and everything associated with the project, search order numbers and everything associated with the order, search assets by names and or numbers, 

The database should be user-friendly, efficient, and highly secure. The ideal candidate should have expertise in database design, development, and optimization. 

   Responsibilities:

   - Design and develop a database to manage parts inventory

   - Design and develop a database that can manage suppliers product catalogue

   - Develop capabilites to place order to suppliers via their product catalogue that is stored in the database

   - Design and develop a database that can manage all company assets, including save all ongoing data entry for each asset.

   - Design and develop search engines within the database, this will be capable of seraching parts, assets, orders, projects etc

   - Implement an intuitive user interface for easy data entry and retrieval

   - Ensure data integrity and security

   - Optimize database performance for efficient data storage and retrieval

   

   Skills required:

   - Proficiency in database development and management

   - Strong knowledge of SQL and relational database concepts

   - Experience with database design and optimization

   - Familiarity with logistics and inventory management systems

   This is a medium-sized project that is expected to take around 3 to 6 months to complete. We are looking for an intermediate-level database developer with a proven track record in similar projects.

title: Salesforce Data Cloud Architecture Consultation - Upwork
description:
We are attempting to use Salesforce Data Cloud to enable payment of pending transactions to customers/independent contractors. Our main problem is we need to create records in Data Cloud, and we're concerned about the risk of overwriting with a calculated insight.

At a high level, our current strategy is outlined below:

1. We plan to have a Data Lake Object (DLO) called “Payment Transactions” (Table A).

2. We want to use a Payments Calculated (CI) (Table B) Insight to process new transactions.

3. We want this CI to write these new payment records and add a payment ID to, ideally, another DLO in Data Cloud (Table C), but we aren’t certain if that would work.

4. Once the new payment records are written in the DLO (or alternative), then it would update the Payment Transactions DLO (Table A-Updated) with the payment ID created through the process and change the transaction status to “Payment Created”

I've attached Payment_Transaction_Tables_Flows.png which helps describe the above.

I've also attached an image with Lucidchart in the title which is a diagram/flowchart of how this would look.

What we need:

1.) Consultation and validation of our strategy.

2.) Advice on how to implement, if needed.

We will handle the implementation ourselves. Since we are not familiar with Data Cloud, we just need an expert to help advise and mitigate any concerns.

title: Mint and transfer Solana NFTs when triggerd by a webhook - Upwork
description:
The idea is roughly to reward Solana users that paid more than amount X of a given token type to one of a few given Solana addresses with a special NFT.

See a rough description in the attached sequence diagram.

--

A user does a transaction (payment) on the Solana blockchain to a small set of specific (hard-coded) target Solana addresses.

A webhook (e.g. Helius WebHook) detects that transaction and sends (as https post) either the transaction hash (ID) or  transaction hash (ID)  and the transaction details to your program.

Your program processes this webhook request, extracts the transaction details performs some simple checks. If conditions are met, your program needs to send an NFT (non-fungible token) to the respective Solana address from the given transaction hash.

The whole process should take less than 7 seconds.

Your node.js program should run in a serverless way (e.g. AWS Lambda, GCP CloudRun or something similar)

Regarding NFT:  it's currently unclear to me whether it's better to mint them on-demand or mint them upfront and just fetch one of those when needed. 

Disclaimer: currently the artwork has not yet been done. We can test it with some very cheap or free NFTs.

FYI: I've set a fixed price. But we can discuss. Let me know what you think.
skills: Node.js,     JavaScript,     Solana,     web3.js,     Serverless Computing

5. The python script needs to be modified to connect and udpate the paramters and results in an RDS database 

6. the python script needs to be modified to push the scrapped data to s3 bucket and apply user sharing polices 

7. the python script will return the final s3 bucket url via email or push notification when everything is done 

8. once the s3 is updated with latest data, the instanced should be tear down 

We are open for better suggestions and looking for experts only. Please ask for more details or questions you have.

title: Full Stack Developer for Platform Development - Upwork
description:
Brief Discription:  We are looking for a skilled individual or team to build a platform similar to jarvislabs.ai. 

The platform will require integrating various APIs, building a user-friendly interface web application.

It will require expertise in the following areas:

backend development, frontend development, DevOps, and UI/UX design. Candidates can apply for specific roles they are skilled in or for multiple roles if they have the necessary expertise.

Detailed Description: 

Project Overview:

Today, there is a plethora of powerful AI software, such as Stable Diffusion, which have substantial market demand and a large pool of skilled users. These products have the potential to attract a vast number of customers. However, two significant issues must be addressed to meet this demand effectively:

i) Complex Installation and Setup:

Most AI products require intricate installation and setup processes, typically involving terminal commands and dependency management. This presents a major hurdle for many AI artists and users who lack a coding background, making it difficult for them to acquire the necessary technical expertise. The frequent updates and new products further complicate this issue, each requiring different installation and setup procedures.

ii) High System Requirements:

Many AI and ML products demand high-performance systems with advanced graphics and video cards, which are not typically available to average laptop or PC users. Therefore, scalable, cloud-based GPU-intensive systems are essential.

These challenges present an opportunity to develop a platform that addresses both issues.

Project Vision:

We aim to create a platform that enables the use of these AI products on any standard laptop or PC with ease. Our platform will feature:

i) Cloud-Based GPU-Intensive Scalable Remote Systems for rental:

Initially, we will leverage existing instances from platforms like Vast.ai, Vultr.com, lambdalabs.com etc., using their APIs. Once we have a substantial customer base and a proven business model, we will consider deploying our own machines.

ii) User-Friendly GUI Interface:

The platform will offer a GUI-based interface for the installation, execution, and automation of AI applications and models on our remote instances. This interface will allow users to install, run, and control applications with minimal effort, similar to how Pinokio.computer operates. Pinokio.computer is open-source and can be adapted for use with our rented instances.

Technical Scope:

The primary technical challenge lies in developing a Pinokio-like GUI system for instances rented from Vast.ai, Vultr.com, lambdalabs.com etc.,. Given that Pinokio.computer is open-source and we have access to Jarvislabs.ai's open-source code base, this task should not be overly complex or time-consuming. Our platform aims to be a more advanced version of Jarvislabs.com.

Proposal Requirements:

We invite you to explore the mentioned platforms (Pinokio.computer, Jarvislabs.ai, and other similar platforms like Replicate.com) and submit a comprehensive proposal. Your proposal should include:

A detailed plan

Software architecture

Team composition

Budget

Timeline

Your proposal will help us shortlist candidates for interviews.

Please start your reply with “I have read everything above” else i will consider it spam. Also you must first understand our upcoming platform and explain your potential role in its development.

title: Developer for Bidirectional Synchronization between AirTable and Pipedrive - Upwork

We are looking for an experienced developer to set up a bidirectional synchronization between AirTable and Pipedrive. This synchronization will cover contacts, deals, and activities from Pipedrive. We have around 150 fields that need to be sync.

The tasks will include:

 - Setting up real-time (or very short interval) synchronization between AirTable and Pipedrive.

 - Handling CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) for data entries.

 - Implementing a system to avoid data duplication during synchronization.

- Implement monitoring and alerting mechanisms to ensure the integrity and performance of the synchronization.

 - Optimizing to ensure the database, currently containing fewer than 5 entries, remains efficiently synchronized as it grows.

Deliverables:

 - Functional bidirectional synchronization between AirTable and Pipedrive.

 - Documentation of the synchronization process and operations performed.

 - Assurance of no duplicates in synchronized data.

 - Code documentation to ensure it can be taken over by another developer if necessary in the future.

Required Skills:

 - Experience with AirTable and Pipedrive.

 - Skills in developing integrations and managing APIs.

 - Proficiency in Python or using Make (Integromat) for integrations.

 - Ability to implement solutions for duplicate data management.

- Availability for future support post-implementation.

- Excellent communication and documentation skills.

To apply, please provide:

- Answer with "Orange" to be sure that you have read the whole job post

- Examples of projects you have worked on involving Airtable and/or Pipedrive

- A brief description of your proposed approach for this project.

- A estimated total cost and numbers of works hours needed for this project.

We look forward to collaborating with you. Thank you for your interest.

Have a great day
